hod, data collection and processing method, possible data collection weaknesses); 9 the assessment results, which describe: q phenomena; q vulnerabilities; q impact; q problems; q causes of problems; q prognoses; q the state of the need for assistance and its probable evolution; q affected populations (who, where, how many, cultural features, functional classifi cation); 9 proposals and recommendations for action; 9 technical attachments. # NUTRITION MANUAL Chapter X -Assessment and planning\n3.1 Setting priorities II."